Market Analysis and Insights

Global Non-Alcoholic Wine Market

Non-alcoholic wine market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to grow at a CAGR of 6.79% in the above-mentioned forecast period. Shifting customer focus towards a healthy lifestyle, coupled with changing diet patterns to consume nutrient-rich products has been directly impacting the growth of non-alcoholic wine market.

Non-alcoholic beer refers to alcoholic beverages prepared for the fermentation of ingredients such as springs, hop, water, and sometimes yeast (speeding up the process). The production of non-alcoholic beer is carried out under a controlled extraction process at set temperatures and pH. Alcohol removal is done by various techniques such as vacuum distillation, reverse osmosis, or by inhibiting the ability of yeast to boiling wort. Every brewery has its ways and secrets to trade in non-alcoholic beer. The definition of non-alcoholic beer varies from country to country.

Rising concerns over adverse health implications associated with consumption of alcoholic drinks are projected to upscale the utility of alternative drinks including functional beverages and soft drinks are the main driving factor for the non-alcoholic wine market. The increasing population of working people, gym-goers, and athletes is expected to promote the demand for nutritious drinks, which will increase their performance as well as keep their energy level high throughout the day is also a driver for the non-alcoholic wine market. Rising awareness regarding healthy diets such as fresh fruit juice, raw food diet, and the paleo diet is an opportunity for the non-alcoholic wine market.

Various government policies are a challenge for the growth of the non-alcoholic wine market. However, the availability of substitute beverages in the carbonated and natural based form is prognosticated is the main restraint for the non-alcoholic wine market during the forecast period of 2021-2028.

